name: ResultType
title: Google
Datastore
V1
EntityResult
ResultType
description: Specifies what data the ‘entity’ field contains. A +ResultType+ is either implied (for example, in +LookupResponse.missing+ from +datastore.proto+, it is always +KEY_ONLY+) or specified by context (for example, in message +QueryResultBatch+, field +entity_result_type+ specifies a +ResultType+ for all the values in field +entity_results+).
